%
% \begin{tikzpicture}[tdplot_main_coords]
%
%
%     % draw the arc
%     \draw[domain=\start:\end,variable=\t,smooth,samples=20,black] plot ({\r*cos(\t)},{\r*sin(\t)},0);
%
% \end{tikzpicture}
%
% \end{document}
% ```
% In this example, we first set the main coordinates using `\tdplotsetmaincoords{70}{110}` to specify the viewing angle. Then, we define the parameters for the arc: the radius, center, and start and end angles. Finally, we draw the arc using the `\draw` command and specifying the domain, variable, and samples to ensure a smooth curved appearance.
